{
  "message": "test(fuzz): extend csv_parse corpus with 7 structured edge-case seeds\n\nThe csv_parse fuzz corpus had 3 seeds (simple, quoted_newline,\nduplicate_headers). Add 7 more to broaden coverage:\n\n- empty_cells_seed: consecutive commas, missing trailing newline cell\n- numeric_columns_seed: floats and ints in separate columns\n- escaped_quotes_seed: RFC-4180 doubled-quote escaping inside a field\n- single_column_seed: width-1 frame\n- header_only_seed: header followed by no rows\n- trailing_whitespace_seed: leading/trailing spaces around cells\n- many_columns_seed: 10 columns, multi-row body\n\nEach seed exercises fuzz_csv_parse_bytes -> read_csv_str ->\nassert_csv_roundtrip, validating both parse and round-trip stability.\nAll 10 csv_parse fuzz seeds (3 prior + 7 new) pass.\n\n[bd-frankenpandas-ylbdp]\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.7 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>",
